		<h3>Design Considerations</h3>
		<p>As the teams main 3d modeller and artist for our project Stealth Raves,
		it is important that I could bring the ideas of my clients and teams’ ideas
		to a visual level. This created a lot of design considerations that I had to
		make, lots of feedback from the client and team have been provided to me and
		I will discuss the direction I went and why. Our client has provided images
		and references of the tower block and environment of the area from the time
		frame we are trying to stay faithful to.
		<br>
		<br>
		The design considerations for Stealth Raves were significantly influenced by
		the vibrant and iconic 90s rave aesthetic, particularly in East London, my
		aim was to capture the essence of this era. Main influences can be seen in my
		design choices of graffiti-adorned walls (figure 1). The incorporation of elements
		like distinctive street art, was a vital step in shaping the game’s visual style.</p>
		<br>
		
